Cloudbees competition - deploy and tweet to donate and win !

What you will need:
- JDK6
- Maven 3 installed
- sense of humor


To enter:

1. Fork this project !

2. git clone and run "mvn bees:run" on the command line - check it works on your machine http://localhost:8080/instructions.html
and http://localhost:8080/ (the latter is what you will publish to the world).

3. Construct your masterpiece (or leave it as it is if you like) - the more creative the better.
Take a look at index.html for starters.

4. Sign-up to www.cloudbees.com - you will need your account name (1), and api key/secret to go any further.
Once signed up - you can go to https://grandcentral.cloudbees.com/user/keys to get your api keys.

5. run "mvn bees:deploy" (will ask for your keys - paste them in from your account Security keys page as asked).
It will ask your for your account name (from when you signed up) - also think of an app name (2).

6. App will deploy - browse to your deployed app: http://page_name(2).account_name(1).cloudbees.net/instructions.html

7. Following the instructions.html page - tweet it to your friends. The more RTs the better.
